# Auto deploy (Vercel via GitHub main)

When the user asks for a feature, fix, or UI change in this project:

1. Complete the implementation and verify build (`npm run build`) when practical.
2. **Do not ask** whether to commit, push, or deploy — the user has approved automatic deploy.
3. After meaningful completed work, commit relevant files and `git push origin main` so Vercel redeploys.
4. Do not commit secrets (`.env`, credentials). Skip unrelated local-only folders (e.g. `.claude/`).
5. Briefly tell the user deploy was pushed; mention any one-time Supabase/manual steps still required (migrations, buckets).

Only skip auto-deploy when the user explicitly says not to push, or when there are no code changes to ship.
